 their joy in the written word."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAmerican poetryy21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican poetryy21st century. 0aPoetryxAuthorshipxCollaboration. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPoetry & Criticism. 7aPOETRY / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh1 aBall, Angela.1 aLehman, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLehman, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilson, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Robert.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171550140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501715501423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501715501.jpg  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles